.TH RSYNC-MNT "1" "October 2018" "dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rsync-mnt \- rsync-mnt
.SH DESCRIPTION
Backups mounted volumes and user directories.
.PP
Files are backed up using rsync to a mounted 'backup' volume, searched in the
specified order from:
.IP
/mnt/
/media/*/
/Volumes/
.PP
Backed up locations include directories in:
.IP
/mnt/
/media/*/
/Volumes/
/home/
/Users/
.PP
Except for directories that are not readable, the name contains a word 'backup',
or the root directory contains a '.rsync\-exclude' file.
.PP
Some operating system related files are automatically excluded from the root
directory when taking a backup, including:
.TP
\&.AppleDB
\&.AppleDesktop    .AppleDouble     .DocumentRevisions\-V100
.TP
\&.fseventsd
\&.Spotlight\-V100  .TemporaryItems  .Trash\-1000
.TP
\&.Trashes
lost+found       ._*
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
$ rsync\-mnt [options] [rsync options]
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print this message
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version number
.SS "Example:"
.IP
$ rsync\-mnt \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
